                        <h2 class="section-heading">FEMINISM</h2>
                        <p>Feminism is a movement that promotes equality between both sexes, men and women. The first wave of feminism came in the 19th and 20th century because of women suffrage. The second wave (1960-1980) began with debate about cultural inequalities, gender norms, and the role of women within society. The third wave (1990-2000s) is more of a continuation of the second wave of feminism and refers to the strain of feminist activity. <br> <br>
                        While feminism has only recently gained such a large following, as well as a large acceptance amongst men and women, we still have extreme lengths to cover. Women are still paid less. Men are still expected to hold a firm masculinity and not show emotion or interest in anything "unmanly". Breaking down these standards and norms will be difficult, but we can only hope that in the future, with the help of feminists, we can get to that point.  </p>
