                    <h2 class="section-heading">LGBTQ+</h2>
                    <p>The LGBTQ+ community consists of people of all genders, sexualities, and identities. LGBT people have been around since the dawn of time, but only recently have people felt safe enough to feel proud of who they are. One thing that really got the LGBT movement started was The Stonewall Riot. The Stonewall Riot happened on June 28th, 1969 at the Stonewall Inn when a group of the LGBT community finally stood up against the unfair ways police berated and treated members of their community. It is said to be the single most important gay rights liberation act in history and paved the way from the LGBT community and rights. <br><br> Now, LGBT people are more accepted and others are much more welcoming but there are still oppressive individuals out there. Children are still being kicked out of their homes for being gay or trans*. People are still getting fired from their workplaces because of how they identify or who they love. And now, we have more government officals trying to take away the rights we've only just gotten. The fight is long from over, but with the help and acceptance from allies and other members of the community, we will not be silenced.  </p>
